cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and the development of universal sentence representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning and transfer learning, which are common topics in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of embeddings in NLP, which is a common topic in information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV), making cs.CV and cs.IR possible sub-categories.
